data.title: Monica Seles - Age, Family, Bio
data.meta_description: Monica Seles: her birthday, what she did before fame, her family life, fun trivia facts, popularity rankings, and more.
data.text:
About

Member of the International Tennis Hall of Fame who won nine Grand Slam titles. She bravely returned to pro tennis after being stabbed during a 1993 match by a crazed fan of her opposition, Steffi Graf. She did not officially retire until 2008.

Before Fame

She began playing tennis when she was five, under the tutelage of her father Karolj Seles, a professional cartoonist.

Trivia

She won the 1990 French Open at the age of 16, setting a record for the youngest French Open champion ever. In 2009, she was elected to the International Tennis Hall of Fame.

Family Life

She was born in Yugoslavia to Karolj and Esther Seles.
